<Author>DaveGow
<Content>GOOD VALUE CONSIDERING THE GREAT LOCATION Have stayed in this hotel about 7 times over the last 23 years, usually for 2 weeks at a time. Had not stayed there for the last 6 years due to better package deals using other hotels. Was apprehensive when I saw that recent reviews suggested it had gone down in quality, and it was missing from a few UK brochures, previously have been given a good 3 star rating bt Kuoni and British Airways. Decided to give it one last bash, had already booked flight via Edinburgh Travel agent who managed to find the hotel being sold via Quantas Airline holidays brochure, they were wllling to sell the hotel alone at bargain of 拢25 per person per night. Had as always, great 2 weeks holiday in our beloved Singapore for the 16th time, melt into the country, you will love it, nicer people are hard to find anywhere on the plant.Anyway, I digress.... the hotel had not really changed, room was fine, overall hotel getting a little shabby, but if you are the type that want 4/5 star hotels on holiday and enjoy the luxury, then its not for you. Staff smile away, a friendly smile to them usually helps, sometimes the formal nature of business that the Chinese race uses, can be off-putting for westerners, in particular Hong Kong, once you understand that, then they dont seems so informal, just different culture. But...if you want a solid hotel with all the basics while you spend most of each day out of it, then the Landmark hits all the right notes. Gym nothing to write home about, pool best in morning as in shade afternoon. The huge factor is LOCATION !!!, I have stayed over the years in most areas of Singers, and this always draws us back. Main roads either side of the hotel give you perfect bus connections either direction on the one way system. The MRT tube train station at Bugis, is about 300 yards away. The shopping in this area is excellent, Bugis Street market (day  night) nearby (eat in the food court within - it is now great value, was a tourist rip-off for long enough). Below the hotel is a 3 level shopping arcade well worth a visit, plenty of late night shops nearby. Loads of eating options in the Arab Street area opposite the front of the hotel. We shall be back to Singers next year as usual, and the Golden Landmark will do fine. Its like an old favourite coat to us, getting shabbier, but does the business and hits all the basic points you need, in the best location in Singers. Over the last 23 years I have watched Singapore hotels getting more expensive as its occupancy rate is very high, being a huge transit stop-over desination. So, getting this hotel in this location is a bargain. Being a good Scotsman, I much prefer to channel the saved money from not going to a fancier hotel, into holiday entertainment on the ground, Camera, Jewellery and food, no contest - gimme the Landmark !!!!, arf arf. Some people like the Hotel Limo to meet them instead of far cheaper airport Taxi, some like champagne in their room etc, depends how you cut your cloth, some people even like to indulge themselves in a bloody cruise where they chomp and drink their way on a long metal boat for 2 weeks, visit various ports, trip off onto a bus and see that Country for 3 hours, then back on the boat, enough said on that !!!, ahem..Each to their own - So, have no fear, go without over-expectation of the Landmark Hotel, and you will be more than pleasantly surprised when you realise how you have landed in the best area to pivot your way around.Hae fun..........arf 
